{"session_id":"svc-1778085235561988669","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-06T16:33:57.641279799Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","work_dir":"/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-4ab66676-20260506T163353-ba20f527","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260506T163353-ba20f527/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260506T163353-ba20f527/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If you write `.ddx/executions/20260506T163353-ba20f527/no_changes_rationale.txt`, it MUST carry one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;one-line shell command\u0026gt;` — the loop runs it (cwd = project root, 60s); exit 0 closes the bead, non-zero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: needs_investigation` + `reason: \u0026lt;why\u0026gt;` — bead stays open for triage.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Bare rationales (\u0026#34;nothing to do\u0026#34;) are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260506T163353-ba20f527/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260506T163353-ba20f527/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Bead overrides project defaults\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead description and AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and conservative project defaults (YAGNI, DOWITYTD, no-docs-unless-asked) in this worktree — write whatever the bead asks for.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-4ab66676\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003ecli: translate SIGINT/SIGTERM into graceful ddx cancellation\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;Ctrl-C / SIGTERM should trigger DDx cooperative cancellation for `ddx work` and `ddx try`, but the CLI root currently executes without a signal-backed context. Operators see abrupt termination rather than an explicit shutdown message and cleanup path.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\u0026#xA;- cli/main.go:31 calls `cmd.Execute(workingDir)` and relies on the default process signal behavior.\u0026#xA;- cli/cmd/root.go:31-39 initializes the root command and calls `rootCmd.Execute()` instead of `ExecuteContext(ctx)`.\u0026#xA;- cli/cmd/work.go:37-40 advertises `signal` as a stop condition, but no production signal handler cancels `cmd.Context()`.\u0026#xA;- docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-010-task-execution.md:423-434 and docs/helix/02-design/solution-designs/SD-025-task-execution-lifecycle.md:177-190 require first-signal cooperative shutdown and the exact operator message `Cancel received, shutting down gracefully`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;- Install a root SIGINT/SIGTERM handler for production CLI execution using `signal.NotifyContext` or equivalent.\u0026#xA;- Execute Cobra with the signal-backed context.\u0026#xA;- On first signal, print `Cancel received, shutting down gracefully` exactly once to the operator-visible stream before cancellation-dependent cleanup begins.\u0026#xA;- On a second signal, hard-abort or restore default signal behavior so wedged cleanup can still be killed.\u0026#xA;- Keep tests deterministic by exposing a small helper/seam rather than sending real OS signals where unit tests can use a cancellable context.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Do not decide bead cleanup policy here beyond propagating context cancellation.\u0026#xA;- Do not change server worker stop/watchdog behavior.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. Production root command execution uses a SIGINT/SIGTERM-backed context and calls ExecuteContext.\u0026#xA;2. First signal prints exactly `Cancel received, shutting down gracefully` once, visible to the operator.\u0026#xA;3. Second signal hard-aborts or restores default signal behavior; the behavior is documented in a source comment and covered by a focused test where practical.\u0026#xA;4. TestRootSignal_FirstInterruptCancelsContextAndPrintsGracefulMessage verifies cancellation and exact message without relying on slow real-time sleeps.\u0026#xA;5. TestRootSignal_MessagePrintedOnce verifies repeated first-path cancellation does not duplicate the message.\u0026#xA;6. Existing command tests that use ExecuteContext continue to control cancellation explicitly.\u0026#xA;7. `cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./cmd/... -run \u0026#34;TestRootSignal|TestWork|TestTry|TestExecuteLoop\u0026#34; -count=1` passes.\u0026#xA;8. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, area:cli, area:agent, kind:bug, reliability, spec:FEAT-010, spec:SD-025, interrupt\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-99a3be32\" spec-id=\"FEAT-010\" base-rev=\"799c60228eff72de5ffb5eae650f8c24eedefd29\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260506T163353-ba20f527\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"FEAT-010\" path=\"docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-010-task-execution.md\"\u003eFeature: Task Execution\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"attempt_id":"20260506T163353-ba20f527","base_rev":"799c60228eff72de5ffb5eae650f8c24eedefd29","bead_id":"ddx-4ab66676","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260506T163353-ba20f527","correlation_id":"ddx-4ab66676:20260506T163353-ba20f527","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260506T163353-ba20f527/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"a1c0f4b82270a77d99c5940625c79bae6b88d6f0ccc040301359739bde4eb440","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-a98d5682","worker_id":""}}}
